    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-08-21T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-08-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="593"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d593">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/6431: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hayes</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-08-21T21:00:00+02:00"
                            >August 21, 1942—9 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 22—2:31 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1159. My 1149, August 20, 10 p.m. If Orgaz has not yet forwarded <hi
                        rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> to Madrid I believe it would be advisable
                    for Childs to amend it by omitting last paragraph substance of which could be
                    conveyed to General Orgaz orally. I am sure Childs could give a reasonable
                    explanation of his action.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Tangier.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hayes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
